#### Issue details
I am developing a game in which I need to play 2 Music instances at the same time. On Desktop they both run at the same time, no problem. On Android however they don't, I did not find anything online related to this issue so I am posting it here. I tried using both Gdx.audio.newMusic() and AssetManager and both methods did not work. I am compiling Java 8 with Retrolambda on a One Plus 3 with Android 7.0 Nougat, buildToolsVersion 25.0.2 and compileSdkVersion 24.

#### Reproduction steps/code
Here is a code sample. This code play both songs on Desktop but not on Android

```java    
Music test1;
Music test2;

AssetManager manager = new AssetManager();

@Override public void create()
{
    manager.load("reversion.mp3", Music.class);
    manager.load("collapse.mp3", Music.class);

    while (!manager.update()) {}
    manager.finishLoading();

    test1 = manager.get("reversion.mp3");
    test2 = manager.get("collapse.mp3");

    test1.setVolume(1);
    test1.play();
    test2.setVolume(1);
    test2.play();
}
```

